Heat the oil in a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the bacon, garlic and onion and fry for 3-4 minutes, or until the bacon begins to brown and the onion softens.Add the thyme and fry for a further minute. Add the beans and stock to the pan and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.Transfer the soup to a blender or food processor and blend with the parsley and pepper until smooth.Return the soup to the pan and heat through, then ladle into 4 bowls and serve immediately.